Meeting a blind person
who instead found Gutenberg

00:03:06.121 --> 00:03:09.510
an important resource was exciting.

00:03:10.109 --> 00:03:15.491
So, I contacted her in DM
and pushed her to apply

00:03:15.601 --> 00:03:18.101
as speaker
for the next WordCamp Italia.

00:03:21.587 --> 00:03:22.587
Elena.

00:03:24.218 --> 00:03:31.195
<v Elena Brescacin> I have been very,
very surprised to be invited to WordCamp.

00:03:31.789 --> 00:03:37.740
I was just replying to the support request
into Facebook about

00:03:37.859 --> 00:03:42.540
one of many Italian support communities.

00:03:43.948 --> 00:03:48.668
It's called SOSWP.

00:03:48.698 --> 00:03:51.509
It's an Italian community

00:03:52.530 --> 00:04:01.258
that makes business by WordPress support,
and she invited me to speak

00:04:01.259 --> 00:04:02.619
to that WordCamp.

00:04:05.479 --> 00:04:09.832
I could say,
what could I do in that field?

00:04:09.987 --> 00:04:12.660
Because I was very,

00:04:12.719 --> 00:04:15.690
very rusty in the use of WordPress.

00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:21.990
I was very, very, let's say,
rusty because I did not know

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:23.680
what to do.

00:04:23.969 --> 00:04:26.259
Gutenberg was quite new for me,

00:04:26.759 --> 00:04:34.529
but I already discovered it
was accessible via keyboard,

00:04:37.109 --> 00:04:45.883
so I caught the chance
and I spoke to the WordCamp.

00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:49.919
Gloria has believed in me

00:04:51.030 --> 00:04:54.149
and I took it to the next level,

00:04:54.500 --> 00:05:00.084
bringing to the WordPress 2021
online WordCamp.

00:05:01.349 --> 00:05:06.563
Explaining how Gutenberg
was used as a content editor

00:05:07.848 --> 00:05:10.252
through Markdown syntax.

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:12.479
It was very, very easy.

00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:17.010
I just pasted Markdown files
into the editor

00:05:17.011 --> 00:05:26.657
and it automatically processed
headings, titles, links, etc.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:30.690
I had superpowers then in editing files

00:05:31.259 --> 00:05:34.020
and I was pleased
to share it with the public.

00:05:43.732 --> 00:05:45.172
<v Gloria> Full site editing.

00:05:45.412 --> 00:05:52.694
So, full site editing will change
how everyone uses themes

00:05:53.430 --> 00:05:55.442
and how we build them,

00:05:56.159 --> 00:05:59.448
but what is full site editing?

00:05:59.609 --> 00:06:02.909
Site editing is
a set of new WordPress features

00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:08.910
that help us build and edit
all parts of our website using blocks.

00:06:09.420 --> 00:06:12.509
Site editor, global styles, block themes,

00:06:13.079 --> 00:06:15.839
patterns, and theme.json.

00:06:16.649 --> 00:06:22.290
Fullsiteediting.com is
an educational resource for learning

00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:23.674
about the features.

00:06:25.219 --> 00:06:30.206
I have been following Project Gutenberg
for several years.

00:06:31.590 --> 00:06:32.909
On a theoretical level,

00:06:32.999 --> 00:06:36.990
I also follow the introduction of the FSE.

00:06:38.489 --> 00:06:40.799
The first time I used it for real

00:06:41.520 --> 00:06:46.050
was the realization
of the WordCamp Torino 2023 website.

00:06:47.039 --> 00:06:55.709
Then I gave a speech at Verona 2023
on how to take the first step with FSE.

00:06:56.549 --> 00:07:03.269
Finally, I was part
of the WCEU 2024 website team

00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:08.279
and I learned to practice templates
and then blocks very well.

00:07:10.260 --> 00:07:11.260
Elena.

00:07:12.095 --> 00:07:20.362
<v Elena> So, I heard about full site editing
in the online WordCamp 2021,

00:07:20.558 --> 00:07:23.447
where I was a speaker.

00:07:25.289 --> 00:07:28.836
Being charmed by Gutenberg,

00:07:29.039 --> 00:07:33.198
I was very, very enthusiastic
of this further step,

00:07:33.929 --> 00:07:37.470
but it was not ready then.

00:07:38.939 --> 00:07:40.282
I was using

00:07:41.370 --> 00:07:42.380
another theme,

00:07:42.440 --> 00:07:46.020
another template system
that was called GeneratePress

00:07:47.460 --> 00:07:50.129
and it was very, very basic.

00:07:50.329 --> 00:07:52.767
I did not care about layout

00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:53.590
and so on,

00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:58.820
but I had in mind
to switch sooner or later.

00:08:00.661 --> 00:08:08.617
In the years 2022
and 2023, in the meanwhile,

00:08:08.893 --> 00:08:11.796
full site editing came out of beta stage

00:08:12.006 --> 00:08:17.520
and I started to see
what it was all about.

00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:24.076
Then the make.wordpress.org
accessibility rule

00:08:25.796 --> 00:08:31.177
provided information about WordPress
backend being accessible,

00:08:31.467 --> 00:08:38.418
core WordPress backend
being accessible and second level WCAG.

00:08:39.629 --> 00:08:42.011
I was enthusiastic

00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:51.983
because I saw that I could build one
interface like it was,

00:08:54.022 --> 00:08:58.973
let's call it like bricks,
like Lego bricks.

00:09:00.092 --> 00:09:04.164
I could move elements around and so on.

00:09:04.471 --> 00:09:09.293
I was lost because I did not know
about how to use it.

00:09:09.682 --> 00:09:13.213
I needed advice, I needed suggestions.

00:09:13.633 --> 00:09:16.273
I just tried to work,

00:09:16.323 --> 00:09:22.144
to consult the fullsiteediting.com website
by Carolina Nymark,

00:09:22.464 --> 00:09:24.364
sorry for the pronunciation.

00:09:25.034 --> 00:09:32.989
I did not find sufficient help
because it had no accessibility support.

00:09:33.899 --> 00:09:40.134
I just took the chance to say
that it should be done,

00:09:40.532 --> 00:09:46.753
one section dedicated
to creators with disability

00:09:46.783 --> 00:09:50.307
into the Learn WordPress area.

00:09:52.292 --> 00:09:54.241
<v Gloria> Okay, next.

00:09:55.139 --> 00:09:58.879
We often use a page builder

00:09:59.319 --> 00:10:00.439
in the backend,

00:10:00.888 --> 00:10:06.188
but the page builders
are accessibility, Elena?

00:10:07.709 --> 00:10:10.208
<v Elena> Well, this is the question.

00:10:10.209 --> 00:10:12.880
If page builders are accessible or not.

00:10:14.311 --> 00:10:15.311
A page builder,

00:10:15.329 --> 00:10:16.329
a site builder,

00:10:16.709 --> 00:10:19.169
as a definition, is very, very complex.

00:10:19.618 --> 00:10:29.368
It's a very, very complex environment
compared to the normal frontend reading

00:10:29.369 --> 00:10:31.588
information and basic interaction.

00:10:32.638 --> 00:10:34.139
I tried many of them.

00:10:35.987 --> 00:10:40.169
Elementor, Divi, SiteOrigin page builder.

00:10:42.089 --> 00:10:48.028
Now I think Gloria is showing
the equalized digital report

00:10:48.029 --> 00:10:54.687
by an Excel file where the approach
of various page builders

00:10:54.688 --> 00:11:02.120
has been treated in this Excel.

00:11:02.121 --> 00:11:04.229
What's the big deal?

00:11:04.288 --> 00:11:08.911
It's because this report
is about frontend.

00:11:13.199 --> 00:11:18.989
I mean, what developers can do
to make a frontend accessible,

00:11:20.099 --> 00:11:22.709
but as far as I know,

00:11:22.768 --> 00:11:25.709
there is no report,

00:11:25.828 --> 00:11:33.268
no documentation on how backend
is in accessibility,

00:11:33.269 --> 00:11:35.248
how Elementor,

00:11:35.279 --> 00:11:41.008
Divi and so on are facing
the authoring tool

00:11:41.278 --> 00:11:42.959
and accessibility guidelines.

00:11:43.649 --> 00:11:46.199
Gutenberg is the best I have found

00:11:47.098 --> 00:11:50.869
because you can do everything by keyboard.

00:11:55.228 --> 00:11:56.590
I tried Elementor,

00:11:56.591 --> 00:12:03.899
I tried Divi, I tried everyone,
but no one was satisfying me.

00:12:05.148 --> 00:12:11.398
I even found once
the SiteOrigin page builder.

00:12:11.399 --> 00:12:13.258
I think that was the name.

00:12:14.029 --> 00:12:18.762
It was declaring it was accessible,

00:12:19.739 --> 00:12:21.749
priority accessible,

00:12:22.789 --> 00:12:32.323
second priority WCAG accessibility,
but it just had tabindex elements.

00:12:34.098 --> 00:12:38.847
You reached everything by tab,
but you had no heading,

00:12:38.848 --> 00:12:45.019
no semantic HTML or semantic code
to indicate that it was accessible.

00:12:45.268 --> 00:12:46.268
In the end,

00:12:46.318 --> 00:12:53.249
I said bye-bye and waited
for better times,

00:12:53.308 --> 00:12:54.308
and in fact,

00:12:54.749 --> 00:13:00.749
it has come with Gutenberg
and now I am satisfied by Gutenberg.

00:13:04.558 --> 00:13:05.648
<v Gloria> Thank you, Elena.

00:13:05.648 --> 00:13:08.458
<v Elena> Sorry, the Excel, I was forgetting,

00:13:09.119 --> 00:13:11.819
is coming from Equalize Digital.

00:13:15.538 --> 00:13:18.158
I think in their site you can find--

00:13:18.768 --> 00:13:22.340
If blind people
or someone you want to see,

00:13:22.341 --> 00:13:28.637
they can find Equalize Digital
accessibility page builder report

00:13:28.638 --> 00:13:30.388
or something like similar.

00:13:32.579 --> 00:13:33.579
<v Gloria> Perfect.

00:13:34.558 --> 00:13:39.389
Now, the core, teacher-student double
learning experience.

00:13:40.429 --> 00:13:42.269
What's your experience, Elena?

00:13:44.038 --> 00:13:47.801
<v Elena> Well, as I said,

00:13:48.859 --> 00:13:50.479
my relationship

00:13:51.718 --> 00:13:54.238
networking with Gloria has been

00:13:55.798 --> 00:14:01.889
based on each other's mutual trust
and believing in each other.

00:14:02.021 --> 00:14:05.649
She has believed in me
when I spoke to WordCamp,

00:14:06.118 --> 00:14:11.458
and I could believe in her
about full site editing.

00:14:11.459 --> 00:14:17.642
She spoke at WorldCamp
Verona last year, 2023,

00:14:18.148 --> 00:14:24.508
and I had a speech also
into the WorldCamp that was called Blind,

00:14:25.249 --> 00:14:26.499
Blog, Independent.

00:14:28.168 --> 00:14:32.849
I created the word blind
by blog and independent.

00:14:36.559 --> 00:14:44.493
Then I knew that full site editing
was out of beta stage.

00:14:45.508 --> 00:14:50.008
I asked her for help
because as I said before,

00:14:50.009 --> 00:14:51.009
I got lost.

00:14:51.149 --> 00:14:56.254
I got lost because it was not just
the basic interface on Gutenberg.

00:14:57.449 --> 00:15:02.699
My worst experience was
because when I changed from GeneratePress

00:15:02.719 --> 00:15:04.621
to 2024 default theme,

00:15:05.369 --> 00:15:06.959
all my menus disappeared.

00:15:08.159 --> 00:15:10.040
I found the page

00:15:10.679 --> 00:15:15.298
was switched to a default one,
was that I have lost everything.

00:15:16.259 --> 00:15:20.338
So I asked, "Please, Gloria, help me.

00:15:21.208 --> 00:15:22.528
If you can teach me

00:15:24.208 --> 00:15:25.918
the interface and so on."

00:15:27.338 --> 00:15:30.715
Gutenberg is accessible,
has a screen reader support,

00:15:30.716 --> 00:15:36.658
so we can take each other hand by hand
and we will help.

00:15:37.108 --> 00:15:38.108
I thought

00:15:38.339 --> 00:15:45.838
she could be afraid of this experience,
but in the end it went very,

00:15:45.868 --> 00:15:46.868
very smooth.

00:15:46.878 --> 00:15:50.369
Now I let her express her point of view.

00:15:53.458 --> 00:15:58.319
<v Gloria> Okay, teaching
a blind person has been challenging

00:15:58.858 --> 00:16:04.115
because I had to change my method,
replacing the graphic symbols

00:16:04.116 --> 00:16:06.239
explanation with the text names.

00:16:07.319 --> 00:16:10.768
For example, instead of back arrow,

00:16:12.342 --> 00:16:16.138
I had to say, press the button named back.

00:16:17.729 --> 00:16:22.679
I could not use terms
that were familiar to me,

00:16:22.739 --> 00:16:27.568
like hamburger menu for example.

00:16:30.557 --> 00:16:31.557
<v Elena> The pencil.

00:16:31.558 --> 00:16:32.867
She told me editor--
<v Gloria> No, no.

00:16:32.867 --> 00:16:39.384
Maybe I show the back end.

00:16:39.385 --> 00:16:40.385
I lost.

00:16:41.628 --> 00:16:44.070
I'm exciting and I'm lost.

00:16:47.447 --> 00:16:56.048
Now I found the hamburger menu.

00:16:59.398 --> 00:17:00.398
I repeat.

00:17:01.019 --> 00:17:02.019
Hamburger menu,

00:17:04.798 --> 00:17:06.028
which corresponds

00:17:06.702 --> 00:17:08.129
to menu action,

00:17:08.578 --> 00:17:14.339
or another terms--

00:17:22.799 --> 00:17:28.928
Sorry, I don't found the--

00:17:29.359 --> 00:17:35.470
Okay, fine, or the pencil icon.

00:17:35.471 --> 00:17:38.668
The pencil icon which corresponds
to edit element.

00:17:39.282 --> 00:17:43.228
This term I could not use.

00:17:43.799 --> 00:17:50.059
One of the difficulty was
that the screen reader detect content

00:17:53.190 --> 00:17:59.428
that I could see on the screen
because it was above the fold.

00:18:01.739 --> 00:18:08.668
I therefore had to ask Elena
to move the tab so that I could see

00:18:08.728 --> 00:18:10.079
what she was doing.

00:18:16.549 --> 00:18:17.549
The glossary.

00:18:20.039 --> 00:18:24.989
To prepare a glossary accessible
to both blind and sight people

00:18:25.259 --> 00:18:27.179
required discussions.

00:18:27.748 --> 00:18:32.649
What worked for Elena
did not work for me and the opposite.

00:18:34.049 --> 00:18:38.699
Now Elena tells you
which compromise we found.

00:18:40.569 --> 00:18:41.569
<v Elena> Yes.

00:18:42.658 --> 00:18:45.459
Let me say that I have tried

00:18:47.988 --> 00:18:49.738
many strategies for the glossary.

00:18:49.927 --> 00:18:51.779
I used the plugin,

00:18:52.529 --> 00:18:57.688
the Code8 was the pronunciation,
plugin glossary,

00:18:59.639 --> 00:19:02.399
but it did not satisfy me,

00:19:03.569 --> 00:19:06.658
especially for back end accessibility.

00:19:07.288 --> 00:19:12.619
It's not so accurated,
accessibility of its back end.

00:19:13.059 --> 00:19:19.289
I said I want to create a simple one,
a page with terms and so on.

00:19:20.129 --> 00:19:25.799
The problem came because I needed
to place the navigation letter,

00:19:25.946 --> 00:19:27.726
the alphabet letters.

00:19:28.199 --> 00:19:33.479
For me, it was very functional
to have a list of letters before.

00:19:36.257 --> 00:19:37.799
The first element could be

00:19:38.549 --> 00:19:40.017
the navigation letters,

00:19:40.018 --> 00:19:46.563
then all the terms and that's all.

00:19:46.965 --> 00:19:50.010
Headings, one heading
level two for the letter,

00:19:50.079 --> 00:19:54.519
and one heading level three
for the corresponding term.

00:19:55.019 --> 00:20:04.918
With after each term a back to menu link
to go back to the navigation.

00:20:06.059 --> 00:20:09.814
If it could be functional
for screen reader users

00:20:09.864 --> 00:20:14.808
because it was easy to jump among
the links and the headings.

00:20:16.068 --> 00:20:17.419
For a sighted person,

00:20:17.478 --> 00:20:18.478
the experience

00:20:19.668 --> 00:20:26.929
was not friendly at all because you had
the screen going back and forth,

00:20:27.379 --> 00:20:29.628
changing the page,

00:20:30.049 --> 00:20:37.727
and the glossary could be very important
to understand the technical terms

00:20:37.937 --> 00:20:41.408
to not create misunderstandings and so on.

00:20:42.168 --> 00:20:53.058
It had to be a friendly experience
for both target audience.

00:20:53.118 --> 00:20:56.267
So me and Gloria,

00:20:56.268 --> 00:21:02.208
I had to explain her screen reader logic,

00:21:02.239 --> 00:21:09.138
and that's why I called
my speech Same Editor,

00:21:09.161 --> 00:21:10.161
Same Language,

00:21:10.218 --> 00:21:15.628
because Gutenberg has
the same structure of a screen reader.

00:21:15.629 --> 00:21:17.039
If you have, for example,

00:21:17.119 --> 00:21:20.208
the blocks list view,

00:21:21.307 --> 00:21:23.989
you will see that it's a tree structure.

00:21:25.248 --> 00:21:27.228
If you have the column group,

00:21:28.219 --> 00:21:30.078
you have column one

00:21:30.978 --> 00:21:34.458
and under column one there is column two.

00:21:35.208 --> 00:21:37.609
I had no trouble to tell Gloria, look

00:21:39.539 --> 00:21:44.779
the logical order is not correct
because you have column one

